news.title: Ghaziabad's master plan: More housing near expressways
news.para: In the Ghaziabad Master Plan 2031, which will come into force in the latter half of the year, residential land use has been increased to 42% from 41.5% in the previous plan (Master Plan 2021).

news.title: China Evergrande gets order to demolish 39 under-construction residential buildings
news.para: Evergrande is struggling to repay more than $300 billion in liabilities, including nearly $20 billion of offshore bonds deemed in cross-default by ratings agencies last month after it missed payments.

news.title: Over 44 lakh houses given to poor in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: A government spokesperson said under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, 17.02 lakh houses have been constructed in urban areas while 26.15 lakh houses got allotted to beneficiaries in rural areas.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: No property tax on homes up to 500 sq ft
news.para: Interestingly, a proposal mooted by Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation (NMMC) for the waiver has been pending at the UD department for over two years.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet minister hints at property tax waiver for other cities too
news.para: “Gradually, the entire state is expected to get the benefit (of waiver). It is just a beginning, as Mumbai has shown the way. We will sit together and decide the future course of action,” said the senior Shiv Sena leader during his official tour to Aurangabad.

news.title: Properties linked to Unitech money laundering being dissipated, says ED
news.para: ED has recorded the statement of Yogesh Gupta, a consultants of the Kore/Trikar Group, and also a close confidant of the Chandras of Unitech. According to the agency, the Trikar/Kore Group is "beneficially owned" and controlled by the Chandra family, especially Sanjay Chandra and his wife, Preeti Chandra.

news.title: Gujarat RERA extends annual report deadline to March 31, 2022
news.para: The deadline has now been extended to March 31, 2022, from December 31, 2021, and will provide relief to developers affected by the Covid-19 pandemic.

news.title: MGF Group booked on charges of cheating: M3M counsel to court
news.para: ​An FIR of cheating and forgery was lodged at the Gurugram City police station on a court order, an M3M counsel told a sessions court during the hearing of an MGF Group's plea, challenging the magisterial court's order for the registration of the FIR.

news.title: RLDA invites bid for residential development in Prayagraj
news.para: This proposed site for residential development is rectangular in shape and is well connected to an extensive network of rail, road, and air. It is about 25 kilometer away from the Prayagraj airport, while the Jhusi railway station is situated just in front of the proposed site.

news.title: Institutional investments in real estate down 17% in 2021 at $4 billion: Report
news.para: As per the data, the institutional investments in office assets fell to USD 1,248 million last year from USD 2,199 million in 2020 calendar year. Similarly, the inflows in mixed-use development projects dipped to USD 182 million from USD 1,616 million.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to invest Rs 110 crore to redevelop housing society in Mumbai
news.para: "The company will invest approximately Rs 110 crore to redevelop the housing project as part of its plan to expand footprint and build residential properties in key prime markets of Mumbai," Ajmera Realty said in a statement.

news.title: Corbett director issued show-cause notice over illegal constructions
news.para: The move came a day after former chief wildlife warden of the state, JS Suhag, had been issued a show-cause notice by additional chief secretary Anand Bardhan for failing to use his authority to stop the illegalities.

news.title: Poor urban design eats into 28% of urban land in Ahmedabad: Study
news.para: Overall in Ahmedabad, a study carried out by CEPT University students under City Studio project found that there are 28% such unutilized open spaces.

news.title: Architects want say in urban planning, write to Punjab CM
news.para: Goel, who is also chairman of the Punjab Architects Association, has suggested to the CM that projects be made for the entire city instead of select areas.

news.title: Seventeen families from TNUHDB tenements collapsed at Tiruvottiyur allotted alternate units
news.para: While the remaining 11 families have sought houses in the same premises at Tiruvottiyur after reconstruction, the release said, financial assistance of Rs. 24,000 would be given to the respective families for staying elsewhere during the reconstruction period.
